headline: Dick Cheney, former US vice president and 'father' of Iraq war, has died
description: During President George W. Bush's two terms, Cheney, a foreign policy hawk who was deeply influenced by conservative ideas, embodied the excesses of the war on terror. He died at the age of 84, his family announced on November 4.

headline: How New York became a nightmare for Airbnb
description: 'The Airbnb Ogre' (6/6). For the past two years, short-term tourist rentals have effectively been banned in the American metropolis as the result of a massively complex regulatory overhaul. The platform is now hoping, without much optimism, to see the rules eased after the municipal elections on Tuesday.

headline: 'There's almost no water left': On the front lines of climate change in southern France
description: A planet at +1.5°C 6/6. Persistent drought, record temperatures, wildfires: Faced with the most acute effects of global warming, residents of the Aude department in southern France are looking for ways to keep their region alive.

headline: Too old to get a job, too young to retire: The French women over 50 stuck in limbo
description: In France, 21% of people aged 55-61 struggle to find work but are unable to retire. Women, who suffer more from societal inequalities throughout their career, are particularly at risk.
